{
  "video_id": "QoTSdOkjEVs",
  "title": "Ron McCallum: How technology allowed me to read",
  "es": 0,
  "json": [
    {
      "index": 1,
      "start_time": 12737.0,
      "end_time": 17270.0,
      "text": "When I was about three or four years old,"
    },
    {
      "index": 2,
      "start_time": 17270.0,
      "end_time": 20909.0,
      "text": "I remember my mum reading a story to me"
    },
    {
      "index": 3,
      "start_time": 20909.0,
      "end_time": 23624.0,
      "text": "and my two big brothers,"
    },
    {
      "index": 4,
      "start_time": 23624.0,
      "end_time": 25643.0,
      "text": "and I remember putting up my hands"
    },
    {
      "index": 5,
      "start_time": 25643.0,
      "end_time": 27646.0,
      "text": "to feel the page of the book,"
    },
    {
      "index": 6,
      "start_time": 27646.0,
      "end_time": 31177.0,
      "text": "to feel the picture they were discussing."
    },
    {
      "index": 7,
      "start_time": 31177.0,
      "end_time": 33626.0,
      "text": "And my mum said, \"Darling,"
    },
    {
      "index": 8,
      "start_time": 33626.0,
      "end_time": 36479.0,
      "text": "remember that you can&#39;t see"
    },
    {
      "index": 9,
      "start_time": 36479.0,
      "end_time": 39525.0,
      "text": "and you can&#39;t feel the picture"
    },
    {
      "index": 10,
      "start_time": 39525.0,
      "end_time": 42461.0,
      "text": "and you can&#39;t feel the print on the page.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 11,
      "start_time": 42462.0,
      "end_time": 44236.0,
      "text": "And I thought to myself,"
    },
    {
      "index": 12,
      "start_time": 44236.0,
      "end_time": 46131.0,
      "text": "\"But that&#39;s what I want to do."
    },
    {
      "index": 13,
      "start_time": 46131.0,
      "end_time": 50292.0,
      "text": "I love stories. I want to read.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 14,
      "start_time": 50292.0,
      "end_time": 52554.0,
      "text": "Little did I know"
    },
    {
      "index": 15,
      "start_time": 52554.0,
      "end_time": 55730.0,
      "text": "that I would be part of a technological revolution"
    },
    {
      "index": 16,
      "start_time": 55730.0,
      "end_time": 58774.0,
      "text": "that would make that dream come true."
    },
    {
      "index": 17,
      "start_time": 58774.0,
      "end_time": 62191.0,
      "text": "I was born premature by about 10 weeks,"
    },
    {
      "index": 18,
      "start_time": 62191.0,
      "end_time": 66836.0,
      "text": "which resulted in my blindness, some 64 years ago."
    },
    {
      "index": 19,
      "start_time": 66836.0,
      "end_time": 69706.0,
      "text": "The condition is known as retrolental fibroplasia,"
    },
    {
      "index": 20,
      "start_time": 69706.0,
      "end_time": 73591.0,
      "text": "and it&#39;s now very rare in the developed world."
    },
    {
      "index": 21,
      "start_time": 73591.0,
      "end_time": 76500.0,
      "text": "Little did I know, lying curled up"
    },
    {
      "index": 22,
      "start_time": 76500.0,
      "end_time": 81293.0,
      "text": "in my prim baby humidicrib in 1948"
    },
    {
      "index": 23,
      "start_time": 81293.0,
      "end_time": 84121.0,
      "text": "that I&#39;d been born at the right place"
    },
    {
      "index": 24,
      "start_time": 84121.0,
      "end_time": 86686.0,
      "text": "and the right time,"
    },
    {
      "index": 25,
      "start_time": 86686.0,
      "end_time": 90570.0,
      "text": "that I was in a country where I could participate"
    },
    {
      "index": 26,
      "start_time": 90570.0,
      "end_time": 93502.0,
      "text": "in the technological revolution."
    },
    {
      "index": 27,
      "start_time": 93503.0,
      "end_time": 98944.0,
      "text": "There are 37 million totally blind people on our planet,"
    },
    {
      "index": 28,
      "start_time": 98944.0,
      "end_time": 102168.0,
      "text": "but those of us who&#39;ve shared in the technological changes"
    },
    {
      "index": 29,
      "start_time": 102168.0,
      "end_time": 105172.0,
      "text": "mainly come from North America, Europe,"
    },
    {
      "index": 30,
      "start_time": 105172.0,
      "end_time": 109597.0,
      "text": "Japan and other developed parts of the world."
    },
    {
      "index": 31,
      "start_time": 109597.0,
      "end_time": 112770.0,
      "text": "Computers have changed the lives of us all in this room"
    },
    {
      "index": 32,
      "start_time": 112770.0,
      "end_time": 113673.0,
      "text": "and around the world,"
    },
    {
      "index": 33,
      "start_time": 113673.0,
      "end_time": 115340.0,
      "text": "but I think they&#39;ve changed the lives"
    },
    {
      "index": 34,
      "start_time": 115340.0,
      "end_time": 118883.0,
      "text": "of we blind people more than any other group."
    },
    {
      "index": 35,
      "start_time": 118883.0,
      "end_time": 122161.0,
      "text": "And so I want to tell you about the interaction"
    },
    {
      "index": 36,
      "start_time": 122161.0,
      "end_time": 125213.0,
      "text": "between computer-based adaptive technology"
    },
    {
      "index": 37,
      "start_time": 125213.0,
      "end_time": 129875.0,
      "text": "and the many volunteers who helped me over the years"
    },
    {
      "index": 38,
      "start_time": 129875.0,
      "end_time": 133276.0,
      "text": "to become the person I am today."
    },
    {
      "index": 39,
      "start_time": 133276.0,
      "end_time": 135910.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s an interaction between volunteers,"
    },
    {
      "index": 40,
      "start_time": 135910.0,
      "end_time": 138831.0,
      "text": "passionate inventors and technology,"
    },
    {
      "index": 41,
      "start_time": 138831.0,
      "end_time": 141766.0,
      "text": "and it&#39;s a story that many other blind people could tell."
    },
    {
      "index": 42,
      "start_time": 141766.0,
      "end_time": 146180.0,
      "text": "But let me tell you a bit about it today."
    },
    {
      "index": 43,
      "start_time": 146181.0,
      "end_time": 150700.0,
      "text": "When I was five, I went to school and I learned braille."
    },
    {
      "index": 44,
      "start_time": 150700.0,
      "end_time": 152531.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s an ingenious system of six dots"
    },
    {
      "index": 45,
      "start_time": 152531.0,
      "end_time": 154265.0,
      "text": "that are punched into paper,"
    },
    {
      "index": 46,
      "start_time": 154265.0,
      "end_time": 157652.0,
      "text": "and I can feel them with my fingers."
    },
    {
      "index": 47,
      "start_time": 157652.0,
      "end_time": 160827.0,
      "text": "In fact, I think they&#39;re putting up my grade six report."
    },
    {
      "index": 48,
      "start_time": 160828.0,
      "end_time": 163553.0,
      "text": "I don&#39;t know where Julian Morrow got that from."
    },
    {
      "index": 49,
      "start_time": 163553.0,
      "end_time": 165109.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 50,
      "start_time": 165109.0,
      "end_time": 166930.0,
      "text": "I was pretty good in reading,"
    },
    {
      "index": 51,
      "start_time": 166930.0,
      "end_time": 171890.0,
      "text": "but religion and musical appreciation needed more work."
    },
    {
      "index": 52,
      "start_time": 171890.0,
      "end_time": 173366.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 53,
      "start_time": 173366.0,
      "end_time": 175453.0,
      "text": "When you leave the opera house,"
    },
    {
      "index": 54,
      "start_time": 175453.0,
      "end_time": 178862.0,
      "text": "you&#39;ll find there&#39;s braille signage in the lifts."
    },
    {
      "index": 55,
      "start_time": 178862.0,
      "end_time": 182579.0,
      "text": "Look for it. Have you noticed it?"
    },
    {
      "index": 56,
      "start_time": 182579.0,
      "end_time": 185309.0,
      "text": "I do. I look for it all the time."
    },
    {
      "index": 57,
      "start_time": 185309.0,
      "end_time": 187395.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 58,
      "start_time": 187395.0,
      "end_time": 189734.0,
      "text": "When I was at school,"
    },
    {
      "index": 59,
      "start_time": 189734.0,
      "end_time": 193260.0,
      "text": "the books were transcribed by transcribers,"
    },
    {
      "index": 60,
      "start_time": 193260.0,
      "end_time": 195859.0,
      "text": "voluntary people who punched one dot at a time"
    },
    {
      "index": 61,
      "start_time": 195859.0,
      "end_time": 197527.0,
      "text": "so I&#39;d have volumes to read,"
    },
    {
      "index": 62,
      "start_time": 197527.0,
      "end_time": 199986.0,
      "text": "and that had been going on, mainly by women,"
    },
    {
      "index": 63,
      "start_time": 199986.0,
      "end_time": 202659.0,
      "text": "since the late 19th century in this country,"
    },
    {
      "index": 64,
      "start_time": 202659.0,
      "end_time": 205143.0,
      "text": "but it was the only way I could read."
    },
    {
      "index": 65,
      "start_time": 205143.0,
      "end_time": 207537.0,
      "text": "When I was in high school,"
    },
    {
      "index": 66,
      "start_time": 207537.0,
      "end_time": 211343.0,
      "text": "I got my first Philips reel-to-reel tape recorder,"
    },
    {
      "index": 67,
      "start_time": 211343.0,
      "end_time": 214732.0,
      "text": "and tape recorders became my sort of pre-computer"
    },
    {
      "index": 68,
      "start_time": 214732.0,
      "end_time": 216912.0,
      "text": "medium of learning."
    },
    {
      "index": 69,
      "start_time": 216912.0,
      "end_time": 220510.0,
      "text": "I could have family and friends read me material,"
    },
    {
      "index": 70,
      "start_time": 220510.0,
      "end_time": 222444.0,
      "text": "and I could then read it back"
    },
    {
      "index": 71,
      "start_time": 222444.0,
      "end_time": 225000.0,
      "text": "as many times as I needed."
    },
    {
      "index": 72,
      "start_time": 225000.0,
      "end_time": 226520.0,
      "text": "And it brought me into contact"
    },
    {
      "index": 73,
      "start_time": 226520.0,
      "end_time": 228530.0,
      "text": "with volunteers and helpers."
    },
    {
      "index": 74,
      "start_time": 228530.0,
      "end_time": 233220.0,
      "text": "For example, when I studied at graduate school"
    },
    {
      "index": 75,
      "start_time": 233220.0,
      "end_time": 235259.0,
      "text": "at Queen&#39;s University in Canada,"
    },
    {
      "index": 76,
      "start_time": 235259.0,
      "end_time": 239341.0,
      "text": "the prisoners at the Collins Bay jail agreed to help me."
    },
    {
      "index": 77,
      "start_time": 239342.0,
      "end_time": 242147.0,
      "text": "I gave them a tape recorder, and they read into it."
    },
    {
      "index": 78,
      "start_time": 242147.0,
      "end_time": 243433.0,
      "text": "As one of them said to me,"
    },
    {
      "index": 79,
      "start_time": 243433.0,
      "end_time": 246191.0,
      "text": "\"Ron, we ain&#39;t going anywhere at the moment.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 80,
      "start_time": 246192.0,
      "end_time": 248653.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 81,
      "start_time": 248653.0,
      "end_time": 250958.0,
      "text": "But think of it. These men,"
    },
    {
      "index": 82,
      "start_time": 250958.0,
      "end_time": 254905.0,
      "text": "who hadn&#39;t had the educational opportunities I&#39;d had,"
    },
    {
      "index": 83,
      "start_time": 254905.0,
      "end_time": 259180.0,
      "text": "helped me gain post-graduate qualifications in law"
    },
    {
      "index": 84,
      "start_time": 259180.0,
      "end_time": 262599.0,
      "text": "by their dedicated help."
    },
    {
      "index": 85,
      "start_time": 262600.0,
      "end_time": 264961.0,
      "text": "Well, I went back and became an academic"
    },
    {
      "index": 86,
      "start_time": 264961.0,
      "end_time": 267603.0,
      "text": "at Melbourne&#39;s Monash University,"
    },
    {
      "index": 87,
      "start_time": 267603.0,
      "end_time": 271113.0,
      "text": "and for those 25 years,"
    },
    {
      "index": 88,
      "start_time": 271113.0,
      "end_time": 273926.0,
      "text": "tape recorders were everything to me."
    },
    {
      "index": 89,
      "start_time": 273926.0,
      "end_time": 276377.0,
      "text": "In fact, in my office in 1990,"
    },
    {
      "index": 90,
      "start_time": 276377.0,
      "end_time": 280904.0,
      "text": "I had 18 miles of tape."
    },
    {
      "index": 91,
      "start_time": 280904.0,
      "end_time": 287808.0,
      "text": "Students, family and friends all read me material."
    },
    {
      "index": 92,
      "start_time": 287809.0,
      "end_time": 289346.0,
      "text": "Mrs. Lois Doery,"
    },
    {
      "index": 93,
      "start_time": 289346.0,
      "end_time": 292324.0,
      "text": "whom I later came to call my surrogate mum,"
    },
    {
      "index": 94,
      "start_time": 292324.0,
      "end_time": 295976.0,
      "text": "read me many thousands of hours onto tape."
    },
    {
      "index": 95,
      "start_time": 295976.0,
      "end_time": 298440.0,
      "text": "One of the reasons I agreed to give this talk today"
    },
    {
      "index": 96,
      "start_time": 298440.0,
      "end_time": 300929.0,
      "text": "was that I was hoping that Lois would be here"
    },
    {
      "index": 97,
      "start_time": 300929.0,
      "end_time": 304965.0,
      "text": "so I could introduce you to her and publicly thank her."
    },
    {
      "index": 98,
      "start_time": 304966.0,
      "end_time": 308715.0,
      "text": "But sadly, her health hasn&#39;t permitted her to come today."
    },
    {
      "index": 99,
      "start_time": 308715.0,
      "end_time": 313303.0,
      "text": "But I thank you here, Lois, from this platform."
    },
    {
      "index": 100,
      "start_time": 313303.0,
      "end_time": 320291.0,
      "text": "(Applause)"
    },
    {
      "index": 101,
      "start_time": 325776.0,
      "end_time": 332635.0,
      "text": "I saw my first Apple computer in 1984,"
    },
    {
      "index": 102,
      "start_time": 332635.0,
      "end_time": 334159.0,
      "text": "and I thought to myself,"
    },
    {
      "index": 103,
      "start_time": 334160.0,
      "end_time": 339128.0,
      "text": "\"This thing&#39;s got a glass screen, not much use to me.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 104,
      "start_time": 339128.0,
      "end_time": 343181.0,
      "text": "How very wrong I was."
    },
    {
      "index": 105,
      "start_time": 343182.0,
      "end_time": 347715.0,
      "text": "In 1987, in the month our eldest son Gerard was born,"
    },
    {
      "index": 106,
      "start_time": 347715.0,
      "end_time": 350169.0,
      "text": "I got my first blind computer,"
    },
    {
      "index": 107,
      "start_time": 350169.0,
      "end_time": 353383.0,
      "text": "and it&#39;s actually here."
    },
    {
      "index": 108,
      "start_time": 353383.0,
      "end_time": 355318.0,
      "text": "See it up there?"
    },
    {
      "index": 109,
      "start_time": 355318.0,
      "end_time": 359601.0,
      "text": "And you see it has no, what do you call it, no screen."
    },
    {
      "index": 110,
      "start_time": 359601.0,
      "end_time": 363919.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 111,
      "start_time": 363919.0,
      "end_time": 365913.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s a blind computer."
    },
    {
      "index": 112,
      "start_time": 365913.0,
      "end_time": 367813.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 113,
      "start_time": 367813.0,
      "end_time": 370418.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s a Keynote Gold 84k,"
    },
    {
      "index": 114,
      "start_time": 370418.0,
      "end_time": 374594.0,
      "text": "and the 84k stands for it had 84 kilobytes of memory."
    },
    {
      "index": 115,
      "start_time": 374594.0,
      "end_time": 377495.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 116,
      "start_time": 377495.0,
      "end_time": 382433.0,
      "text": "Don&#39;t laugh, it cost me 4,000 dollars at the time. (Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 117,
      "start_time": 382433.0,
      "end_time": 387127.0,
      "text": "I think there&#39;s more memory in my watch."
    },
    {
      "index": 118,
      "start_time": 387127.0,
      "end_time": 390147.0,
      "text": "It was invented by Russell Smith, a passionate inventor"
    },
    {
      "index": 119,
      "start_time": 390147.0,
      "end_time": 392945.0,
      "text": "in New Zealand who was trying to help blind people."
    },
    {
      "index": 120,
      "start_time": 392945.0,
      "end_time": 396747.0,
      "text": "Sadly, he died in a light plane crash in 2005,"
    },
    {
      "index": 121,
      "start_time": 396747.0,
      "end_time": 399605.0,
      "text": "but his memory lives on in my heart."
    },
    {
      "index": 122,
      "start_time": 399605.0,
      "end_time": 401857.0,
      "text": "It meant, for the first time,"
    },
    {
      "index": 123,
      "start_time": 401857.0,
      "end_time": 405188.0,
      "text": "I could read back what I had typed into it."
    },
    {
      "index": 124,
      "start_time": 405188.0,
      "end_time": 407145.0,
      "text": "It had a speech synthesizer."
    },
    {
      "index": 125,
      "start_time": 407145.0,
      "end_time": 409405.0,
      "text": "I&#39;d written my first coauthored labor law book"
    },
    {
      "index": 126,
      "start_time": 409405.0,
      "end_time": 414231.0,
      "text": "on a typewriter in 1979 purely from memory."
    },
    {
      "index": 127,
      "start_time": 414231.0,
      "end_time": 418542.0,
      "text": "This now allowed me to read back what I&#39;d written"
    },
    {
      "index": 128,
      "start_time": 418542.0,
      "end_time": 420219.0,
      "text": "and to enter the computer world,"
    },
    {
      "index": 129,
      "start_time": 420220.0,
      "end_time": 423620.0,
      "text": "even with its 84k of memory."
    },
    {
      "index": 130,
      "start_time": 423620.0,
      "end_time": 429800.0,
      "text": "In 1974, the great Ray Kurzweil, the American inventor,"
    },
    {
      "index": 131,
      "start_time": 429800.0,
      "end_time": 431758.0,
      "text": "worked on building a machine that would scan books"
    },
    {
      "index": 132,
      "start_time": 431758.0,
      "end_time": 434289.0,
      "text": "and read them out in synthetic speech."
    },
    {
      "index": 133,
      "start_time": 434289.0,
      "end_time": 436836.0,
      "text": "Optical character recognition units then"
    },
    {
      "index": 134,
      "start_time": 436836.0,
      "end_time": 439576.0,
      "text": "only operated usually on one font,"
    },
    {
      "index": 135,
      "start_time": 439576.0,
      "end_time": 443920.0,
      "text": "but by using charge-coupled device flatbed scanners"
    },
    {
      "index": 136,
      "start_time": 443920.0,
      "end_time": 445426.0,
      "text": "and speech synthesizers,"
    },
    {
      "index": 137,
      "start_time": 445426.0,
      "end_time": 449832.0,
      "text": "he developed a machine that could read any font."
    },
    {
      "index": 138,
      "start_time": 449832.0,
      "end_time": 452962.0,
      "text": "And his machine, which was as big as a washing machine,"
    },
    {
      "index": 139,
      "start_time": 452963.0,
      "end_time": 456937.0,
      "text": "was launched on the 13th of January, 1976."
    },
    {
      "index": 140,
      "start_time": 456937.0,
      "end_time": 460200.0,
      "text": "I saw my first commercially available Kurzweil"
    },
    {
      "index": 141,
      "start_time": 460200.0,
      "end_time": 463327.0,
      "text": "in March 1989, and it blew me away,"
    },
    {
      "index": 142,
      "start_time": 463327.0,
      "end_time": 466117.0,
      "text": "and in September 1989,"
    },
    {
      "index": 143,
      "start_time": 466117.0,
      "end_time": 469310.0,
      "text": "the month that my associate professorship"
    },
    {
      "index": 144,
      "start_time": 469310.0,
      "end_time": 471282.0,
      "text": "at Monash University was announced,"
    },
    {
      "index": 145,
      "start_time": 471282.0,
      "end_time": 475140.0,
      "text": "the law school got one, and I could use it."
    },
    {
      "index": 146,
      "start_time": 475140.0,
      "end_time": 479173.0,
      "text": "For the first time, I could read what I wanted to read"
    },
    {
      "index": 147,
      "start_time": 479173.0,
      "end_time": 480581.0,
      "text": "by putting a book on the scanner."
    },
    {
      "index": 148,
      "start_time": 480581.0,
      "end_time": 483297.0,
      "text": "I didn&#39;t have to be nice to people!"
    },
    {
      "index": 149,
      "start_time": 483297.0,
      "end_time": 485940.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 150,
      "start_time": 485940.0,
      "end_time": 488890.0,
      "text": "I no longer would be censored."
    },
    {
      "index": 151,
      "start_time": 488890.0,
      "end_time": 491130.0,
      "text": "For example, I was too shy then,"
    },
    {
      "index": 152,
      "start_time": 491130.0,
      "end_time": 493602.0,
      "text": "and I&#39;m actually too shy now, to ask anybody"
    },
    {
      "index": 153,
      "start_time": 493602.0,
      "end_time": 496414.0,
      "text": "to read me out loud sexually explicit material."
    },
    {
      "index": 154,
      "start_time": 496415.0,
      "end_time": 500387.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 155,
      "start_time": 500387.0,
      "end_time": 503875.0,
      "text": "But, you know, I could pop a book on in the middle of the night, and --"
    },
    {
      "index": 156,
      "start_time": 503875.0,
      "end_time": 509598.0,
      "text": "(Laughter) (Applause)"
    },
    {
      "index": 157,
      "start_time": 513528.0,
      "end_time": 516712.0,
      "text": "Now, the Kurzweil reader is simply"
    },
    {
      "index": 158,
      "start_time": 516712.0,
      "end_time": 518996.0,
      "text": "a program on my laptop."
    },
    {
      "index": 159,
      "start_time": 518996.0,
      "end_time": 520340.0,
      "text": "That&#39;s what it&#39;s shrunk to."
    },
    {
      "index": 160,
      "start_time": 520340.00000000006,
      "end_time": 522430.00000000006,
      "text": "And now I can scan the latest novel"
    },
    {
      "index": 161,
      "start_time": 522429.0,
      "end_time": 524635.0,
      "text": "and not wait to get it into talking book libraries."
    },
    {
      "index": 162,
      "start_time": 524635.0,
      "end_time": 527896.0,
      "text": "I can keep up with my friends."
    },
    {
      "index": 163,
      "start_time": 527896.0,
      "end_time": 531136.0,
      "text": "There are many people who have helped me in my life,"
    },
    {
      "index": 164,
      "start_time": 531136.0,
      "end_time": 533766.0,
      "text": "and many that I haven&#39;t met."
    },
    {
      "index": 165,
      "start_time": 533767.0,
      "end_time": 537416.0,
      "text": "One is another American inventor Ted Henter."
    },
    {
      "index": 166,
      "start_time": 537416.0,
      "end_time": 539788.0,
      "text": "Ted was a motorcycle racer,"
    },
    {
      "index": 167,
      "start_time": 539788.0,
      "end_time": 544200.0,
      "text": "but in 1978 he had a car accident and lost his sight,"
    },
    {
      "index": 168,
      "start_time": 544200.0,
      "end_time": 547579.0,
      "text": "which is devastating if you&#39;re trying to ride motorbikes."
    },
    {
      "index": 169,
      "start_time": 547579.0,
      "end_time": 550375.0,
      "text": "He then turned to being a waterskier"
    },
    {
      "index": 170,
      "start_time": 550375.0,
      "end_time": 553887.0,
      "text": "and was a champion disabled waterskier."
    },
    {
      "index": 171,
      "start_time": 553887.0,
      "end_time": 557133.0,
      "text": "But in 1989, he teamed up with Bill Joyce"
    },
    {
      "index": 172,
      "start_time": 557134.0,
      "end_time": 561269.0,
      "text": "to develop a program that would read out"
    },
    {
      "index": 173,
      "start_time": 561269.0,
      "end_time": 563200.0,
      "text": "what was on the computer screen"
    },
    {
      "index": 174,
      "start_time": 563200.0,
      "end_time": 565240.0,
      "text": "from the Net or from what was on the computer."
    },
    {
      "index": 175,
      "start_time": 565240.0,
      "end_time": 568531.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s called JAWS, Job Access With Speech,"
    },
    {
      "index": 176,
      "start_time": 568531.0,
      "end_time": 570535.0,
      "text": "and it sounds like this."
    },
    {
      "index": 177,
      "start_time": 570535.0,
      "end_time": 574420.0,
      "text": "(JAWS speaking)"
    },
    {
      "index": 178,
      "start_time": 581985.0,
      "end_time": 583748.0,
      "text": "Ron McCallum: Isn&#39;t that slow?"
    },
    {
      "index": 179,
      "start_time": 583748.0,
      "end_time": 584718.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 180,
      "start_time": 584718.0,
      "end_time": 586986.0,
      "text": "You see, if I read like that, I&#39;d fall asleep."
    },
    {
      "index": 181,
      "start_time": 586986.0,
      "end_time": 588194.0,
      "text": "I slowed it down for you."
    },
    {
      "index": 182,
      "start_time": 588195.0,
      "end_time": 591467.0,
      "text": "I&#39;m going to ask that we play it at the speed I read it."
    },
    {
      "index": 183,
      "start_time": 591467.0,
      "end_time": 593982.0,
      "text": "Can we play that one?"
    },
    {
      "index": 184,
      "start_time": 593982.0,
      "end_time": 598737.0,
      "text": "(JAWS speaking)"
    },
    {
      "index": 185,
      "start_time": 607809.0,
      "end_time": 609832.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 186,
      "start_time": 609832.0,
      "end_time": 611653.0,
      "text": "RM: You know, when you&#39;re marking student essays,"
    },
    {
      "index": 187,
      "start_time": 611653.0,
      "end_time": 613570.0,
      "text": "you want to get through them fairly quickly."
    },
    {
      "index": 188,
      "start_time": 613570.0,
      "end_time": 620648.0,
      "text": "(Laughter) (Applause)"
    },
    {
      "index": 189,
      "start_time": 623139.0,
      "end_time": 626722.0,
      "text": "This technology that fascinated me in 1987"
    },
    {
      "index": 190,
      "start_time": 626722.0,
      "end_time": 630443.0,
      "text": "is now on my iPhone and on yours as well."
    },
    {
      "index": 191,
      "start_time": 630443.0,
      "end_time": 633977.0,
      "text": "But, you know, I find reading with machines"
    },
    {
      "index": 192,
      "start_time": 633977.0,
      "end_time": 636390.0,
      "text": "a very lonely process."
    },
    {
      "index": 193,
      "start_time": 636390.0,
      "end_time": 641329.0,
      "text": "I grew up with family, friends, reading to me,"
    },
    {
      "index": 194,
      "start_time": 641329.0,
      "end_time": 644247.0,
      "text": "and I loved the warmth and the breath"
    },
    {
      "index": 195,
      "start_time": 644248.0,
      "end_time": 646602.0,
      "text": "and the closeness of people reading."
    },
    {
      "index": 196,
      "start_time": 646602.0,
      "end_time": 648875.0,
      "text": "Do you love being read to?"
    },
    {
      "index": 197,
      "start_time": 648875.0,
      "end_time": 651675.0,
      "text": "And one of my most enduring memories"
    },
    {
      "index": 198,
      "start_time": 651675.0,
      "end_time": 657123.0,
      "text": "is in 1999, Mary reading to me and the children"
    },
    {
      "index": 199,
      "start_time": 657124.0,
      "end_time": 659520.0,
      "text": "down near Manly Beach"
    },
    {
      "index": 200,
      "start_time": 659520.0,
      "end_time": 662925.0,
      "text": "\"Harry Potter and the Philosopher&#39;s Stone.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 201,
      "start_time": 662925.0,
      "end_time": 665228.0,
      "text": "Isn&#39;t that a great book?"
    },
    {
      "index": 202,
      "start_time": 665228.0,
      "end_time": 668600.0,
      "text": "I still love being close to someone reading to me."
    },
    {
      "index": 203,
      "start_time": 668600.0,
      "end_time": 669820.0,
      "text": "But I wouldn&#39;t give up the technology,"
    },
    {
      "index": 204,
      "start_time": 669821.0,
      "end_time": 675111.0,
      "text": "because it&#39;s allowed me to lead a great life."
    },
    {
      "index": 205,
      "start_time": 675111.0,
      "end_time": 677798.0,
      "text": "Of course, talking books for the blind"
    },
    {
      "index": 206,
      "start_time": 677798.0,
      "end_time": 679410.0,
      "text": "predated all this technology."
    },
    {
      "index": 207,
      "start_time": 679410.0,
      "end_time": 682889.0,
      "text": "After all, the long-playing record was developed"
    },
    {
      "index": 208,
      "start_time": 682889.0,
      "end_time": 684278.0,
      "text": "in the early 1930s,"
    },
    {
      "index": 209,
      "start_time": 684278.0,
      "end_time": 686967.0,
      "text": "and now we put talking books on CDs"
    },
    {
      "index": 210,
      "start_time": 686967.0,
      "end_time": 692530.0,
      "text": "using the digital access system known as DAISY."
    },
    {
      "index": 211,
      "start_time": 692530.0,
      "end_time": 695712.0,
      "text": "But when I&#39;m reading with synthetic voices,"
    },
    {
      "index": 212,
      "start_time": 695712.0,
      "end_time": 698662.0,
      "text": "I love to come home and read a racy novel"
    },
    {
      "index": 213,
      "start_time": 698662.0,
      "end_time": 702612.0,
      "text": "with a real voice."
    },
    {
      "index": 214,
      "start_time": 702612.0,
      "end_time": 704684.0,
      "text": "Now there are still barriers"
    },
    {
      "index": 215,
      "start_time": 704684.0,
      "end_time": 706677.0,
      "text": "in front of we people with disabilities."
    },
    {
      "index": 216,
      "start_time": 706677.0,
      "end_time": 709595.0,
      "text": "Many websites we can&#39;t read using JAWS"
    },
    {
      "index": 217,
      "start_time": 709595.0,
      "end_time": 710882.0,
      "text": "and the other technologies."
    },
    {
      "index": 218,
      "start_time": 710882.0,
      "end_time": 713850.0,
      "text": "Websites are often very visual,"
    },
    {
      "index": 219,
      "start_time": 713860.0,
      "end_time": 714533.0,
      "text": "and there are all these sorts of graphs"
    },
    {
      "index": 220,
      "start_time": 714533.0,
      "end_time": 717484.0,
      "text": "that aren&#39;t labeled and buttons that aren&#39;t labeled,"
    },
    {
      "index": 221,
      "start_time": 717484.0,
      "end_time": 721281.0,
      "text": "and that&#39;s why the World Wide Web Consortium 3,"
    },
    {
      "index": 222,
      "start_time": 721281.0,
      "end_time": 726843.0,
      "text": "known as W3C, has developed worldwide standards"
    },
    {
      "index": 223,
      "start_time": 726844.0,
      "end_time": 728258.0,
      "text": "for the Internet."
    },
    {
      "index": 224,
      "start_time": 728258.0,
      "end_time": 733688.0,
      "text": "And we want all Internet users or Internet site owners"
    },
    {
      "index": 225,
      "start_time": 733688.0,
      "end_time": 735910.0,
      "text": "to make their sites compatible so that"
    },
    {
      "index": 226,
      "start_time": 735910.0,
      "end_time": 740586.0,
      "text": "we persons without vision can have a level playing field."
    },
    {
      "index": 227,
      "start_time": 740586.0,
      "end_time": 744641.0,
      "text": "There are other barriers brought about by our laws."
    },
    {
      "index": 228,
      "start_time": 744641.0,
      "end_time": 747189.0,
      "text": "For example, Australia,"
    },
    {
      "index": 229,
      "start_time": 747190.0,
      "end_time": 749682.0,
      "text": "like about one third of the world&#39;s countries,"
    },
    {
      "index": 230,
      "start_time": 749682.0,
      "end_time": 754226.0,
      "text": "has copyright exceptions which allow books to be brailled"
    },
    {
      "index": 231,
      "start_time": 754226.0,
      "end_time": 756398.0,
      "text": "or read for we blind persons."
    },
    {
      "index": 232,
      "start_time": 756398.0,
      "end_time": 759618.0,
      "text": "But those books can&#39;t travel across borders."
    },
    {
      "index": 233,
      "start_time": 759618.0,
      "end_time": 762400.0,
      "text": "For example, in Spain, there are a 100,000"
    },
    {
      "index": 234,
      "start_time": 762400.0,
      "end_time": 764425.0,
      "text": "accessible books in Spanish."
    },
    {
      "index": 235,
      "start_time": 764426.0,
      "end_time": 766804.0,
      "text": "In Argentina, there are 50,000."
    },
    {
      "index": 236,
      "start_time": 766804.0,
      "end_time": 768583.0,
      "text": "In no other Latin American country"
    },
    {
      "index": 237,
      "start_time": 768583.0,
      "end_time": 770660.0,
      "text": "are there more than a couple of thousand."
    },
    {
      "index": 238,
      "start_time": 770660.0,
      "end_time": 772765.0,
      "text": "But it&#39;s not legal to transport the books"
    },
    {
      "index": 239,
      "start_time": 772765.0,
      "end_time": 775590.0,
      "text": "from Spain to Latin America."
    },
    {
      "index": 240,
      "start_time": 775590.0,
      "end_time": 778347.0,
      "text": "There are hundreds of thousands of accessible books"
    },
    {
      "index": 241,
      "start_time": 778347.0,
      "end_time": 781223.0,
      "text": "in the United States, Britain, Canada, Australia, etc.,"
    },
    {
      "index": 242,
      "start_time": 781223.0,
      "end_time": 783911.0,
      "text": "but they can&#39;t be transported to the 60 countries"
    },
    {
      "index": 243,
      "start_time": 783912.0,
      "end_time": 786886.0,
      "text": "in our world where English is the first and the second language."
    },
    {
      "index": 244,
      "start_time": 786886.0,
      "end_time": 790296.0,
      "text": "And remember I was telling you about Harry Potter."
    },
    {
      "index": 245,
      "start_time": 790297.0,
      "end_time": 793411.0,
      "text": "Well, because we can&#39;t transport books across borders,"
    },
    {
      "index": 246,
      "start_time": 793411.0,
      "end_time": 795334.0,
      "text": "there had to be separate versions read"
    },
    {
      "index": 247,
      "start_time": 795335.0,
      "end_time": 798264.0,
      "text": "in all the different English-speaking countries:"
    },
    {
      "index": 248,
      "start_time": 798264.0,
      "end_time": 801315.0,
      "text": "Britain, United States, Canada, Australia,"
    },
    {
      "index": 249,
      "start_time": 801315.0,
      "end_time": 803396.0,
      "text": "and New Zealand all had to have"
    },
    {
      "index": 250,
      "start_time": 803396.0,
      "end_time": 806139.0,
      "text": "separate readings of Harry Potter."
    },
    {
      "index": 251,
      "start_time": 806139.0,
      "end_time": 809253.0,
      "text": "And that&#39;s why, next month in Morocco,"
    },
    {
      "index": 252,
      "start_time": 809253.0,
      "end_time": 811752.0,
      "text": "a meeting is taking place between all the countries."
    },
    {
      "index": 253,
      "start_time": 811752.0,
      "end_time": 813155.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s something that a group of countries"
    },
    {
      "index": 254,
      "start_time": 813155.0,
      "end_time": 815283.0,
      "text": "and the World Blind Union are advocating,"
    },
    {
      "index": 255,
      "start_time": 815283.0,
      "end_time": 817601.0,
      "text": "a cross-border treaty"
    },
    {
      "index": 256,
      "start_time": 817601.0,
      "end_time": 820739.0,
      "text": "so that if books are available under a copyright exception"
    },
    {
      "index": 257,
      "start_time": 820739.0,
      "end_time": 822708.0,
      "text": "and the other country has a copyright exception,"
    },
    {
      "index": 258,
      "start_time": 822708.0,
      "end_time": 825106.0,
      "text": "we can transport those books across borders"
    },
    {
      "index": 259,
      "start_time": 825106.0,
      "end_time": 828322.0,
      "text": "and give life to people, particularly in developing countries,"
    },
    {
      "index": 260,
      "start_time": 828322.0,
      "end_time": 832247.0,
      "text": "blind people who don&#39;t have the books to read."
    },
    {
      "index": 261,
      "start_time": 832247.0,
      "end_time": 834358.0,
      "text": "I want that to happen."
    },
    {
      "index": 262,
      "start_time": 834359.0,
      "end_time": 842598.0,
      "text": "(Applause)"
    },
    {
      "index": 263,
      "start_time": 842598.0,
      "end_time": 845863.0,
      "text": "My life has been extraordinarily blessed"
    },
    {
      "index": 264,
      "start_time": 845863.0,
      "end_time": 848497.0,
      "text": "with marriage and children"
    },
    {
      "index": 265,
      "start_time": 848497.0,
      "end_time": 851575.0,
      "text": "and certainly interesting work to do,"
    },
    {
      "index": 266,
      "start_time": 851576.0,
      "end_time": 854230.0,
      "text": "whether it be at the University of Sydney Law School,"
    },
    {
      "index": 267,
      "start_time": 854230.0,
      "end_time": 855502.0,
      "text": "where I served a term as dean,"
    },
    {
      "index": 268,
      "start_time": 855502.0,
      "end_time": 859220.0,
      "text": "or now as I sit on the United Nations Committee"
    },
    {
      "index": 269,
      "start_time": 859230.0,
      "end_time": 862163.0,
      "text": "on the Rights of Persons with Disabilities, in Geneva."
    },
    {
      "index": 270,
      "start_time": 862163.0,
      "end_time": 867158.0,
      "text": "I&#39;ve indeed been a very fortunate human being."
    },
    {
      "index": 271,
      "start_time": 867158.0,
      "end_time": 870166.0,
      "text": "I wonder what the future will hold."
    },
    {
      "index": 272,
      "start_time": 870166.0,
      "end_time": 873857.0,
      "text": "The technology will advance even further,"
    },
    {
      "index": 273,
      "start_time": 873857.0,
      "end_time": 877525.0,
      "text": "but I can still remember my mum saying, 60 years ago,"
    },
    {
      "index": 274,
      "start_time": 877525.0,
      "end_time": 879459.0,
      "text": "\"Remember, darling,"
    },
    {
      "index": 275,
      "start_time": 879459.0,
      "end_time": 883603.0,
      "text": "you&#39;ll never be able to read the print with your fingers.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 276,
      "start_time": 883604.0,
      "end_time": 888781.0,
      "text": "I&#39;m so glad that the interaction between braille transcribers,"
    },
    {
      "index": 277,
      "start_time": 888781.0,
      "end_time": 891678.0,
      "text": "volunteer readers and passionate inventors,"
    },
    {
      "index": 278,
      "start_time": 891678.0,
      "end_time": 894868.0,
      "text": "has allowed this dream of reading to come true for me"
    },
    {
      "index": 279,
      "start_time": 894868.0,
      "end_time": 897872.0,
      "text": "and for blind people throughout the world."
    },
    {
      "index": 280,
      "start_time": 897872.0,
      "end_time": 901517.0,
      "text": "I&#39;d like to thank my researcher Hannah Martin,"
    },
    {
      "index": 281,
      "start_time": 901518.0,
      "end_time": 904488.0,
      "text": "who is my slide clicker, who clicks the slides,"
    },
    {
      "index": 282,
      "start_time": 904488.0,
      "end_time": 908879.0,
      "text": "and my wife, Professor Mary Crock, who&#39;s the light of my life,"
    },
    {
      "index": 283,
      "start_time": 908879.0,
      "end_time": 910237.0,
      "text": "is coming on to collect me."
    },
    {
      "index": 284,
      "start_time": 910237.0,
      "end_time": 911432.0,
      "text": "I want to thank her too."
    },
    {
      "index": 285,
      "start_time": 911432.0,
      "end_time": 913432.0,
      "text": "I think I have to say goodbye now."
    },
    {
      "index": 286,
      "start_time": 913432.0,
      "end_time": 915300.0,
      "text": "Bless you. Thank you very much."
    },
    {
      "index": 287,
      "start_time": 915300.0,
      "end_time": 916727.0,
      "text": "(Applause)"
    },
    {
      "index": 288,
      "start_time": 916727.0,
      "end_time": 925964.0,
      "text": "Yay! (Applause)"
    },
    {
      "index": 289,
      "start_time": 932602.0,
      "end_time": 938571.0,
      "text": "Okay. Okay. Okay. Okay. Okay. (Applause)"
    }
  ]
}